            <title>[LUDOC-454] Attempt to create existing net returns EINVAL</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-454</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &quot;lnetctl net add&quot; is called for an interface/net pair that already exists, the error code returned is EINVAL.  It should be EEXIST, so the user knows that the net is already configured.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
